{
  "texts": [
    "ResultsPrevious studies have found that learners with different educational backgrounds have different choices of vocabulary strategies.",
    "This research compared the second-year undergraduates with different majors and academic levels.",
    "The results are shown below.",
    "The Characteristics of Vocabulary Learning Strategies Used by Chinese LearnersTable 1 demonstrates that participants use social strategies the least when it comes to vocabulary learning strategies, which suggests that learners are not proficient at learning vocabulary through social communication and cooperation.",
    "Determination, social, memory, cognitive, and metacognitive strategies are effectively divided into these categories."
  ]
}